<span id="freeTextContainer4737050507609573161">An excellent depiction of turn of the century Chicago, as it prospers and grows. Our main character, Selina, grows as well as this novel progresses. We see her as a youngster to a teacher to a married woman to a widow to a prosperous landowner/farmer. We meet Dirk (so Big) her son, to whom she devotes her life. The mother son relationship very well depicted in this book.<br/>This book revolves around making choices-taking the easy route or working hard for what you want and believe in. As Selina&apos;s Da</span>
  <span id="freeText4737050507609573161" style="display:none">An excellent depiction of turn of the century Chicago, as it prospers and grows. Our main character, Selina, grows as well as this novel progresses. We see her as a youngster to a teacher to a married woman to a widow to a prosperous landowner/farmer. We meet Dirk (so Big) her son, to whom she devotes her life. The mother son relationship very well depicted in this book.<br />This book revolves around making choices-taking the easy route or working hard for what you want and believe in. As Selina's Dad told her life is an adventure, whether positive or negative. I liked the strength of Selina and how she never despaired and always sought out the beauty. A good lesson for us all. I know a book has to end somewhere but I would loved for it to have continued as I wanted more!</span>
